A lot of people live with their parents, especially when rent is so expensive and the slump in
很多人和父母住，尤其是房租这么贵，经济又不景气的时候。

17
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:50,080
the economy.


18
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:52,400
Yeah, but you're almost 40.
是啊，但你都快40岁了。

19
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:55,800
Plus, you make good money so there's really no excuse.
而且你收入不错，所以真的没什么借口。

20
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,800
That's just simply because you're a mama's boy.
这纯粹是因为你是个妈宝男。

21
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:58,800
Whatever, dude.
随便你怎么说，哥们。

22
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,280
I have everything I need.
我需要的东西都有。

23
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,680
Why would I move out?
我为什么要搬出去？

24
00:01:01,680 --> 00:01:05,040
Have a great roof over my head, my mom does my laundry and cooks for me.
头顶有好房子住，我妈给我洗衣服做饭。

25
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:06,960
What else could a guy ask for?
一个男人还能要求什么？

26
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:07,960
Let's agree to disagree.
我们求同存异吧。

27
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:11,920
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

28
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:18,000
So now let's take a look at some language on Language Takeaway.
现在来看看“语言要点”中的一些语言点。

29
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,720
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

30
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,160
The first verb we have here is to break up.
我们这里的第一个动词是“分手”。

31
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:26,840
So we heard the guy say, why did your girlfriend break up with you?
我们听到那个男人说：你女朋友为什么和你分手？

32
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:27,840
That's right.
没错。

33
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:33,200
So this is a phrasal verb and to break up in a relationship or in a romantic sense means
这是一个短语动词，在恋爱关系中，“分手”的意思是

34
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,440
to end a relationship.
结束一段关系。

35
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:40,880
So if you break up with your girlfriend, it means you end the relationship.
所以如果你和女朋友分手，意思就是你结束了这段关系。

36
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:41,880
That's right.
没错。

37
00:01:41,880 --> 00:01:43,840
So you think about breaking something, it goes into pieces.
你可以想象“打破”某物，它碎成碎片。

38
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:48,600
Well, in a relationship, it means you both leave each other, you go your separate ways.
嗯，在关系中，它意味着你们彼此离开，各走各的路。

39
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:53,140
And so you can say, he broke up with me or we broke up.
所以你可以说：他和我分手了，或者我们分手了。

40
00:01:53,140 --> 00:01:54,160
That's right.
没错。

41
00:01:54,160 --> 00:02:01,960
And the reason his girlfriend broke up with him is because she said he was not independent.
他女朋友和他分手的原因是她觉得他不独立。

42
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:05,520
So she wanted him to be more independent.
所以她希望他更独立。

43
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:09,040
So independent means that you do things on your own.
所以“独立”意味着你自己做事。

44
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:11,200
When you're, you know, you do things alone.
当你，你知道，你独自做事。

45
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,640
You don't expect other people to help you.
你不指望别人帮你。

46
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,840
You don't depend on other people.
你不依赖别人。

47
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,840
Exactly.
完全正确。

48
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,860
So you can say, he's very independent.
所以你可以说：他非常独立。

49
00:02:18,860 --> 00:02:20,840
He loves to travel alone.
他喜欢独自旅行。

50
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,840
Okay.
好的。

51
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:25,360
So it means that you don't really need other people's help, I guess, right?
所以它意味着你不太需要别人的帮助，我想，对吧？

52
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,360
Exactly.
完全正确。

53
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,360
Okay.
好的。

54
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,360
All right.
好了。

55
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:31,360
So he's not really very independent and well, his friend agrees.
所以他其实不太独立，嗯，他的朋友也同意。

56
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,360
He says, well, you know what?
他说：嗯，你知道吗？

57
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,880
I think she has a point.
我觉得她说的有道理。

58
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:40,480
To have a point means to say something that the other person agrees with.
“有道理”意思是说了一些对方同意的话。

59
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,480
Okay.
好的。

60
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:44,000
So you could say, he has a point.
所以你可以说：他说的有道理。

61
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,520
I agree with him.
我同意他。

62
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,880
That's a good argument.
这是个好论点。

63
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,880
Right.
对。

64
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:51,960
So if somebody says something and you agree with that, when you say, yeah, you have a
所以如果有人说了什么，你同意，当你说：是啊，你说的

65
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,800
point, it means you agree with the argument.
有道理，意思是你同意这个论点。

66
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,600
You agree with what that person says.
你同意那个人说的话。

67
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:57,600
All right.
好的。

68
00:02:57,600 --> 00:03:03,000
And now lastly, because he lives with his parents, his friend is saying that he should
最后，因为他和父母住，他的朋友说他应该

69
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,160
move out.
搬出去。

70
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,480
You should move out.
你应该搬出去。

71
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:08,000
So here's another phrasal verb, to move out.
所以这里是另一个短语动词，“搬出去”。

72
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:13,120
This means that you leave the house and you find a new house.
这意味着你离开房子，找新房子。

73
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:15,600
So when you're with your parents, you want to move out.
所以当你和父母住时，你想搬出去。

74
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:20,000
That means you don't live with your parents anymore, but you find your own house.
这意味着你不再和父母住，而是找自己的房子。

75
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
That's right.
没错。

76
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,040
So, well, in general, when you find your own house, when you leave and your current place
所以，嗯，一般来说，当你找到自己的房子，离开你现在的

77
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:28,400
of living, that's moving out, right?
住处，那就是搬出去，对吧？

78
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,400
That's right.
没错。

79
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:33,140
So if I'm leaving the city, I move out of my house.
所以如果我要离开城市，我就搬出我的房子。

80
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:36,680
And then when I arrive in a new city, I move in to a new house.
然后当我到达新城市时，我就搬进新房子。

81
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,680
Oh, very good.
哦，很好。

82
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:41,480
So to move out and to move in, they go hand in hand.
所以搬出去和搬进来是相辅相成的。

83
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,480
All right.
好的。

84
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:51,560
So let's listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back with Fluency Builder.
那我们再听一遍对话，然后回来进行流利度训练。

85
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,560
Why did your girlfriend break up with you?
