今天流利度训练开头有一个非常有趣的短语。

107
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:45,560
The phrase is manning up.
这个短语是“manning up”。

108
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:50,000
So the girlfriend was tired of the man not manning up.
所以女朋友厌倦了这个男人不够男子气概。

109
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Right.
对。

110
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,760
So to man up.
所以“to man up”。

111
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,760
And what does that mean?
那是什么意思？

112
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,320
To man up to something?
对某事“man up”？

113
00:04:55,320 --> 00:05:01,480
It means to be responsible or to be more mature or to be an adult about something.
意思是负责任、更成熟或像个成年人一样处理事情。

114
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:06,360
So maybe this guy, this man, he's kind of immature.
所以也许这个家伙，这个男人，有点不成熟。

115
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,880
He lives at home.
他住在家里。

116
00:05:07,880 --> 00:05:10,720
He's not very responsible or independent.
他不太负责任或独立。

117
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:14,880
And his girlfriend wanted him to be more responsible, more independent.
他女朋友希望他更负责任、更独立。

118
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,200
So she wanted him to man up.
所以她希望他“man up”。

119
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:18,200
That's right.
没错。

120
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:22,720
So it usually means that you also should accept the consequences for your actions.
所以通常也意味着你应该为自己的行为承担后果。

121
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,720
Right.
对。

122
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,720
Exactly.
正是。

123
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:29,120
So you might push someone to man up, take responsibility for something and do it even
所以你可能催促某人“man up”，承担责任并去做某事，即使

124
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:33,200
